text.section:
Except as otherwise provided in § 9-501(b), to be sufficient, a financing statement that covers as-extracted collateral or timber to be cut, or which is filed as a fixture filing and covers goods that are or are to become fixtures, must satisfy subsection (a) and also:
Indicate that it covers this type of collateral;
Indicate that it is to be recorded in the land records;
Provide a description of the real property to which the collateral is related; and
If the debtor does not have an interest of record in the real property, provide the name of a record owner.
